<p>You can use the dashboards to manage instances created by other users.</p>
    <p><image href="../../../media/CGH-2-instances.png" width="600" id="image_tfv_jp5_ht"/></p>
<p>Use the <b>Compute</b> panel on the <b>Project</b> dashboard to:</p>
<ul>
<li>
  <xref href="CGH-2-User-Instance-create.dita#topic2817">Create a new instance
  </xref></li>
<li>
  
  <xref href="CGH-2-User-Instance-terminate.dita#topic811">Terminate an instance</xref></li>
<li>

  <xref href="CGH-2-User-Instance-reboot.dita#topic1036">Reboot an instance</xref></li>
<li>

  <xref href="CGH-2-User-Instance-rebuild.dita#topic1314">Rebuild an instance</xref></li>
<li>

  <xref href="CGH-2-User-Instance-suspend.dita#topic1594">Suspend and resume an instance</xref></li>
<li>

  <xref href="CGH-2-User-Instance-pause.dita#topic1643c2uip">Pause and resume an instance</xref>
      </li>
<li>

  <xref href="CGH-2-User-Instance-snapshot-create.dita#topic1162">Create an instance snapshot</xref></li>
</ul>
<p>You can also <xref href="CGH-2-User-assoc-ipaddress.dita#topic2995">associate, or assign, a floating IP address</xref> to an instance. A floating IP address
      makes the instance available on the external network.</p>
